9
00:00:27,720 --> 00:00:29,070
Sure!

10
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:31,240
What's going on?

11
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:33,120
Mom said she'll be living here.

12
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:35,330
What a lovely home!

13
00:00:35,330 --> 00:00:39,060
Saki never did anything around our house. Are you holding up okay, Koichi?

14
00:00:39,060 --> 00:00:41,090
Well, I mean...

15
00:00:41,090 --> 00:00:44,050
<i>You</i> don't do anything around the house.

16
00:00:44,050 --> 00:00:46,090
What's this ballpoint pen?

17
00:00:46,090 --> 00:00:48,350
Oh my god, your name's on it!

18
00:00:49,510 --> 00:00:51,030
For you, this is pretty lame.

19
00:00:51,030 --> 00:00:52,420
Just leave it!

20
00:00:52,420 --> 00:00:53,560
Oh!

21
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:56,970
- This room-
- No, that room is...

22
00:00:56,970 --> 00:00:57,940
- Wait!
- Then that room must...

23
00:00:57,940 --> 00:01:00,670
Wait, Mom! Calm down!

24
00:01:00,670 --> 00:01:02,360
Let's just sit down and talk.

25
00:01:02,360 --> 00:01:03,890
Talk about what?

26
00:01:03,890 --> 00:01:07,020
Why you're living at our place, obviously!

27
00:01:07,020 --> 00:01:09,910
Did you and Dad have a fight?

28
00:01:09,910 --> 00:01:13,160
That man... is having an affair.

29
00:01:14,690 --> 00:01:18,250
I'm getting a divorce!

30
00:01:18,250 --> 00:01:20,140
- Why?
- What?

31
00:01:20,140 --> 00:01:23,680
I mean, he's had lots of affairs before, right?

32
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:25,750
Why are you getting a divorce now?

33
00:01:25,750 --> 00:01:27,630
That man...

34
00:01:28,180 --> 00:01:31,320
<i>Oops, she has some solid evidence of cheating!</i>

35
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:34,470
He said the word he was never to say.

36
00:01:34,470 --> 00:01:37,810
But anyway, let me stay over tonight!

37
00:01:37,810 --> 00:01:40,920
- Hold on...
- Please, please!

38
00:01:40,920 --> 00:01:42,960
Please!

39
00:01:49,090 --> 00:01:51,260
- Excuse me.
- Oh!

40
00:01:51,260 --> 00:01:54,040
- Just put them over there!
- Okay.

41
00:02:00,950 --> 00:02:04,140
- Hold it, hold it!
- What?

42
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:08,280
I haven't told my mom yet

43
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:11,050
about our divorce.

44
00:02:11,050 --> 00:02:14,070
- But...
- If she finds out, it'll be so annoying.

45
00:02:14,070 --> 00:02:17,700
She'll spread rumors and the story will blow up.

46
00:02:18,510 --> 00:02:20,060
That is a problem.

47
00:02:20,060 --> 00:02:23,020
I'll wait for a good moment to tell her.

48
00:02:23,020 --> 00:02:27,110
So for now, can we pretend like things are going well?

49
00:02:30,130 --> 00:02:32,480
Understood!

50
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:36,070
- Then sleep here tonight.
- What?

51
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:41,300
I-It's not like I want to sleep together or anything.

52
00:02:41,300 --> 00:02:43,160
We just don't have a choice.

53
00:02:43,760 --> 00:02:45,840
R-Right...

54
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:50,080
- I'll sleep here.
- What?

55
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:53,600
You can't do that! Sleep here!

56
00:02:57,010 --> 00:03:01,250
I was the one who asked you to be here.

57
00:03:01,910 --> 00:03:03,750
In that case...

58
00:03:27,930 --> 00:03:29,580
Your mom!

59
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:35,050
This seems to be Jinya's official Instagram.

60
00:03:35,050 --> 00:03:38,110
- Jinya?
- It's a famous hot spring inn.

61
00:03:38,110 --> 00:03:40,100
Let me see.

62
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:44,800
<i>[We scrub and wash for our customers today!]</i>

63
00:03:57,900 --> 00:04:01,110
Saki, could you get me another towel?

64
00:04:01,110 --> 00:04:02,220
Oh!

65
00:04:02,220 --> 00:04:03,540
Did I interrupt?

66
00:04:03,540 --> 00:04:05,740
- N-No!
- I-It's totally fine!

67
00:04:05,740 --> 00:04:08,440
Really?

68
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:09,740
Oh?

69
00:04:09,740 --> 00:04:14,600
Is this Jinya? This place is great!

70
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:17,540
Don't tell me... Are you two going on a honeymoon?

71
00:04:17,540 --> 00:04:19,790
Yes, yes, you have to go!

72
00:04:19,790 --> 00:04:22,580
I'll house-sit when you're away!

73
00:04:22,580 --> 00:04:26,470
Honeymoons are so much fun!

74
00:04:26,470 --> 00:04:30,440
It might've been the most fun I had after getting married!

75
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:34,580
Back then, Takeshi didn't pay any attention to other women,

76
00:04:34,580 --> 00:04:37,490
but then he became a womanizer in the blink of an eye!

77
00:04:37,490 --> 00:04:41,130
- Mom, stop.
- I won't be like that!

78
00:04:41,130 --> 00:04:45,020
My! Just what I'd expected from you, Koichi!

79
00:04:45,540 --> 00:04:47,740
Isn't that wonderful, Saki?

80
00:04:47,740 --> 00:04:51,310
Enjoy your honeymoon.

81
00:05:14,300 --> 00:05:15,610
Sorry.

82
00:05:15,610 --> 00:05:17,060
Me too.

83
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:18,690
Sorry...

84
00:05:32,010 --> 00:05:34,140
I want you to go to Hakone and get Mom.

85
00:05:34,140 --> 00:05:35,290
<i>Reject!</i>

86
00:05:35,290 --> 00:05:38,310
Why not? Please go talk with her!

87
00:05:38,310 --> 00:05:40,280
I said I'm not going!

88
00:05:41,310 --> 00:05:42,850
It's beneath a man's dignity!

89
00:05:42,850 --> 00:05:44,860
Hello? Dad?

90
00:05:48,660 --> 00:05:49,840
He's not going.

91
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:51,550
Then...

92
00:05:52,140 --> 00:05:53,710
I'll go there alone.

93
00:05:53,710 --> 00:05:56,300
Then my mom will think something is up.

94
00:05:56,300 --> 00:06:00,150
So you're saying we should go together?

95
00:06:01,510 --> 00:06:02,910
There is no other choice, is there?

96
00:06:02,910 --> 00:06:07,080
- I haven't told her about our divorce yet-
- Good morning!

97
00:06:07,080 --> 00:06:09,170
- Good morning!
- Morning.

98
00:06:09,170 --> 00:06:10,520
Koichi, you're already heading out?

99
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:12,250
It's just 5.30 a.m!

100
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:14,940
I always leave at this time.

101
00:06:14,940 --> 00:06:18,360
So early!

102
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:20,180
Well, excuse me.

103
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:21,270
Yes, yes, yes.

104
00:06:21,270 --> 00:06:23,380
The base is in Ibaraki, right?

105
00:06:23,380 --> 00:06:27,090
It must've been a much closer drive from your parents' house!

106
00:06:27,090 --> 00:06:29,820
Saki liked this place.

107
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:32,770
So Saki is the reason you have such a long commute?

108
00:06:32,770 --> 00:06:34,230
No.

109
00:06:34,230 --> 00:06:35,910
I wanted it.

110
00:06:35,910 --> 00:06:38,250
I couldn't let Saki be the one with a long commute.

111
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:42,250
If anything were to happen to me, Saki would be closer to her family in Tokyo,

112
00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:46,210
so I thought Saki could live more peacefully here.

113
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:48,170
Is that true?

114
00:06:48,170 --> 00:06:52,010
That's amazing! I could cry!

115
00:06:52,010 --> 00:06:54,510
Saki, he really loves you!

116
00:06:54,510 --> 00:06:56,960
You married a good guy.

117
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,640
Well...

118
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:03,480
I'm heading out.

119
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:06,800
Have a good day!

120
00:07:08,250 --> 00:07:11,620
<i>[How to Get a Divorce for the Whole Family!]</i>

121
