<i>[Episode Three]</i>

122
00:07:13,630 --> 00:07:14,860
<i>[Sencho Garden Terrace]</i>

123
00:07:14,860 --> 00:07:17,320
Right, got it.

124
00:07:23,230 --> 00:07:25,910
10 a.m, right? Okay. Talk to you later.
<i>[Saki Obara]</i>

125
00:07:25,910 --> 00:07:28,270
Ms. Obara?

126
00:07:28,270 --> 00:07:31,350
Saki Obara?

127
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:35,480
Saki Obara.

128
00:07:38,470 --> 00:07:40,690
Here. You dropped it.

129
00:07:40,690 --> 00:07:44,360
- Thank yo-Â 
- What a fancy pen, right?

130
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:46,640
I called your name several times, though.

131
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:50,900
I'm sorry. I'm not used to that surname yet.

132
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:54,620
Newlywed? Or divorced?

133
00:07:54,620 --> 00:07:57,760
<i>Both might be true before long.</i>

134
00:07:57,760 --> 00:08:00,910
Newlywed, I guess.

135
00:08:00,910 --> 00:08:04,290
Then do you believe in love?

136
00:08:06,430 --> 00:08:08,650
Congratulations.

137
00:08:09,650 --> 00:08:11,330
Personally...

138
00:08:12,530 --> 00:08:15,610
I don't think love exists.

139
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,980
That's not something you say to a newlywed, I guess.

140
00:08:24,050 --> 00:08:25,770
Thanks for this.

141
00:08:25,770 --> 00:08:28,960
See you around, Saki Obara.

142
00:08:42,210 --> 00:08:43,220
- Good work!
- Good work!

143
00:08:43,220 --> 00:08:46,190
Good work!

144
00:08:48,790 --> 00:08:51,350
- Master Sergeant Obara.
- Yes?

145
00:08:51,770 --> 00:08:54,910
I'm sorry about the barbeque the other day.

146
00:08:54,910 --> 00:08:58,660
Please raise your head, Second Lieutenant. What are you talking about?

147
00:08:58,660 --> 00:09:02,170
Your wife got lost

148
00:09:02,170 --> 00:09:06,500
because she thought I had forgotten something.

149
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:11,170
<i>Never leave my side again!</i>

150
00:09:11,170 --> 00:09:12,810
<i>Why</i>

151
00:09:12,810 --> 00:09:16,660
<i>are you always protecting me?</i>

152
00:09:16,660 --> 00:09:18,340
<i>We're getting a divorce.</i>

153
00:09:18,340 --> 00:09:20,950
<i>I'm still your husband.</i>

154
00:09:20,950 --> 00:09:24,090
Please, don't worry about that.

155
00:09:24,780 --> 00:09:26,550
- But...
- Good work!

156
00:09:26,550 --> 00:09:28,870
- Good work!
- Good work!

157
00:09:28,870 --> 00:09:32,210
Master Sergeant Obara, I approved your vacation request.

158
00:09:32,210 --> 00:09:33,430
Thank you very much!

159
00:09:33,430 --> 00:09:34,750
Is it for your honeymoon?

160
00:09:34,750 --> 00:09:36,950
- W-Well...
- Honeymoon?

161
00:09:36,950 --> 00:09:39,200
Have lots of fun with your wife, you hear?

162
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:41,660
- I can't wait for a honeymoon, baby!
- What?

163
00:09:41,660 --> 00:09:45,050
Master Sergeant, where are you going?

164
00:09:45,050 --> 00:09:46,190
Hakone.

165
00:09:46,190 --> 00:09:48,160
The Jinya inn there is great.

166
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:49,610
You know about it?

167
00:09:49,610 --> 00:09:52,310
What's this? Are you staying at Jinya?!

168
00:09:52,310 --> 00:09:56,050
Let's have a send-off party for Master Sergeant Obara's honeymoon!

169
00:09:56,050 --> 00:09:57,750
- Let's do it!
- Yeah!

170
00:09:57,750 --> 00:10:00,490
N-No, that's not necessary!

171
00:10:02,340 --> 00:10:05,540
Aoyama, do you want to try 100 kilos today?

172
00:10:05,540 --> 00:10:07,070
Yeah.

173
00:10:14,330 --> 00:10:15,560
Hi!

174
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:17,250
Hi.

175
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:29,290
- I can't do it!
- You'll be fine.

176
00:10:29,290 --> 00:10:31,770
I really can't do it!

177
00:10:35,650 --> 00:10:36,780
Obara?

178
00:10:36,780 --> 00:10:38,580
Yes?

179
00:10:38,580 --> 00:10:42,010
What's your wife like?

180
00:10:43,020 --> 00:10:44,120
Sorry for asking so randomly.

181
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:47,740
As a lawyer, all I hear about are divorces.

182
00:10:47,740 --> 00:10:50,520
What made you decide to marry her?

183
00:10:50,520 --> 00:10:53,570
What made her different than the other girls you dated?

184
00:10:53,570 --> 00:10:55,680
I don't know.

185
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:57,650
She was the first woman I dated.

186
00:10:57,650 --> 00:10:59,320
- Really?
- Yes.

187
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:03,600
I just decided to marry the woman I was dating.

188
00:11:07,300 --> 00:11:09,720
- Is that weird?
- No...

189
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:11,230
It's amazing.

190
00:11:11,230 --> 00:11:12,620
What about you, Aoyama?

191
00:11:12,620 --> 00:11:15,580
Well, I've dated a few girls.

192
00:11:15,580 --> 00:11:17,640
My longest relationship

193
00:11:17,640 --> 00:11:20,140
was with my ex-girlfriend who split with me four months ago.

194
00:11:20,140 --> 00:11:21,590
We had the same interests.

195
00:11:21,590 --> 00:11:24,390
I thought our relationship would stay like that forever.

196
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:27,670
But then out of the blue, she said, "I want to get married."

197
00:11:29,250 --> 00:11:31,880
Did you tell your girlfriend too, that you can't get married?

198
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:35,420
I did, then she wanted to break up.

199
00:11:35,420 --> 00:11:37,540
I didn't stop her.

200
00:11:37,540 --> 00:11:40,290
- And then...
- What happened?

201
00:11:40,290 --> 00:11:41,820
She got married.

202
00:11:41,820 --> 00:11:45,440
Out of spite, with a guy she had just met.

203
00:11:48,010 --> 00:11:49,820
It could have been anyone, right?

204
00:11:49,820 --> 00:11:52,280
It was my fault, though.

205
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:55,800
I didn't realize she wanted to get married at all.

206
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:57,800
I still think about it sometimes.

207
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:00,080
When she said she wanted to break up,

208
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:02,790
why didn't I stop her?

209
00:12:07,390 --> 00:12:09,270
Do you still love her?

210
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:11,680
Your ex-girlfriend.

211
00:12:11,680 --> 00:12:14,440
We dated for five years, after all.

212
00:12:18,020 --> 00:12:22,220
<i>The best food at Hakone is the pickled-plum bun at Watanabe Bakery.</i>

213
00:12:22,220 --> 00:12:26,300
The curry donut from Bakery & Table is good too.

214
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:28,320
If we're in the Ashinoko Lake area,

215
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:31,470
maybe we can go on a tour boat!

216
00:12:32,180 --> 00:12:34,810
You seem excited.

217
00:12:34,810 --> 00:12:37,930
Things must be going well with Koichi, right?

218
00:12:37,930 --> 00:12:39,280
I'm so relieved!

219
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:40,930
It's not like that.

220
00:12:40,930 --> 00:12:44,680
Don't they say people get excited in a new environment?

221
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:47,540
You should bring some cute underwear!

222
00:12:47,540 --> 00:12:49,270
What are you talking about?! I told you, it's not like that.

223
00:12:49,270 --> 00:12:50,670
I'm home!

224
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:51,840
- Get this!
- Welcome home.

225
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:54,120
I might be going global!

226
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:55,930
Oh, Natsumi, hello!

227
00:12:55,930 --> 00:12:57,310
I just dropped by.

228
00:12:57,310 --> 00:12:58,650
Going global?

229
00:12:58,650 --> 00:13:00,520
Midori Mizuguchi produced

230
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:03,760
"Venus Mignon", and it's selling like hotcakes!

231
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:07,240
They're thinking of expanding to China!

232
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:11,440
Natsumi, you can have this as a sample!

233
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:14,000
Really? Thank you!

234
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,090
Use it up!

235
00:13:15,090 --> 00:13:18,290
Do you remember that editor who came to our house, Tachikawa?

236
00:13:18,290 --> 00:13:20,120
He's so talented!

237
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:23,560
I can really rely on him!

238
00:13:24,410 --> 00:13:29,280
And here is some takeout from Piatto Suzuki!

239
00:13:31,550 --> 00:13:34,940
Speak of the devil, it's Tachikawa.

240
00:13:34,940 --> 00:13:37,120
Hello? Mizuguchi speaking.

241
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:39,710
Is she living here?

242
00:13:39,710 --> 00:13:41,640
I called Dad, but he said,

243
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:45,190
"If you let her do what she wants, she'll get bored and come home eventually."

244
00:13:45,190 --> 00:13:48,270
That's hard on you too, isn't it?

245
00:13:52,250 --> 00:13:54,820
You must be so excited for Hakone!

246
00:13:54,820 --> 00:13:57,190
- Right, Koichi?
- Yes.

247
00:13:57,190 --> 00:13:58,960
Not exactly.

248
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:02,620
What are you saying? You're so bashful!

249
00:14:03,850 --> 00:14:07,540
W-Wait, Koichi. Aren't you eating too fast?

250
00:14:07,540 --> 00:14:10,410
In the JSDF, eating fast is necessary.

251
00:14:10,410 --> 00:14:13,620
You never know when something will happen.

252
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:25,300
I can do it on my own.

253
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:27,320
There is still a spot!

254
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:29,610
I'll re-wash it, excuse me.

255
00:14:29,610 --> 00:14:32,560
Then you should have done it from the start.

256
00:14:34,230 --> 00:14:35,760
Sparkling clean!

257
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:38,390
It's a rule in the JDSF to polish things until they shine.

258
00:14:38,390 --> 00:14:42,990
The first thing taught to new recruits is how to polish their combat boots.

259
00:14:44,380 --> 00:14:46,940
That's amazing!

260
00:14:47,490 --> 00:14:50,300
"The Little Prince Museum."

261
00:14:50,300 --> 00:14:53,040
"Stroll through the French-style streets and gardens."

262
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:55,350
"Through the world of the story."

263
00:14:55,350 --> 00:14:58,540
- "The Little Prince-"
- Well, I'm going to take a bath and then go to bed!

264
00:14:58,540 --> 00:15:01,470
- H-Have a good night.
- Good night!

265
00:15:03,880 --> 00:15:06,890
The Little Prince was written by San-Exu-oh.

266
00:15:06,890 --> 00:15:08,950
San-Exu-oh!

267
00:15:08,950 --> 00:15:10,020
Wait!

268
00:15:10,020 --> 00:15:11,770
<i>[Hakone]</i>

269
00:15:17,870 --> 00:15:22,010
I think the blouse and pants look prettier in this one.

270
00:15:22,010 --> 00:15:24,540
That's true.

271
00:15:24,540 --> 00:15:26,680
- Saki!
- Yes?

272
00:15:26,680 --> 00:15:29,160
Could you come here for a second?

273
00:15:30,260 --> 00:15:34,000
About you possibly being in charge of the Kira column...

274
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,210
Yes?

275
00:15:35,210 --> 00:15:37,050
<i>I believe...</i>

276
00:15:37,050 --> 00:15:39,980
<i>she will live up to your expectations!</i>

277
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:42,190
<i>What a wonderful partner you've been blessed with.</i>

278
00:15:42,920 --> 00:15:45,380
They weren't sure until the very end,

279
00:15:45,380 --> 00:15:49,520
but they decided to go with someone else.

280
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:51,850
I see.

281
00:15:52,850 --> 00:15:55,780
Actually, we've been discussing this for a while,

282
00:15:55,780 --> 00:15:58,100
and we're going to transfer you.

283
00:15:58,100 --> 00:16:01,760
Starting May 1st, you'll be working for the Literature Department.

284
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:05,320
I want you to take this fresh start

285
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:08,330
and show them how talented you are.

286
00:16:08,910 --> 00:16:10,430
This is a promotion, you know.

287
00:16:10,430 --> 00:16:13,630
The Literature Department props up our sales.

288
00:16:14,420 --> 00:16:16,950
I told them I wanted you to stay here forever,

289
00:16:16,950 --> 00:16:18,540
but it was the company's decision.

290
00:16:18,540 --> 00:16:21,020
I know you'll become the ace for the Literature Department!

291
00:16:21,020 --> 00:16:22,680
Your vacation starts tomorrow, right?

292
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:24,010
You can come back all refreshed.

293
00:16:24,010 --> 00:16:25,460
<i>A flower bouquet!</i>

294
00:16:25,460 --> 00:16:29,380
<i>- It's a meat bouquet!
- Eat it, eat it!</i>

295
00:16:29,380 --> 00:16:31,760
Oh? Your glass is empty, Master Sergeant!

296
00:16:31,760 --> 00:16:33,330
Excuse me, Nao?

297
00:16:33,330 --> 00:16:36,050
- Two beers!
- Well, I'll be going.

298
00:16:36,050 --> 00:16:37,680
You can't leave yet!

299
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:40,050
The party dies when the guest of honor goes home.

300
00:16:40,050 --> 00:16:42,290
But I'm just going to Hakone.

301
00:16:42,290 --> 00:16:43,670
Master Sergeant Obara!

302
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:48,420
Please accept this thoughtful gift!

303
00:16:48,420 --> 00:16:52,080
- Are those bottles of snake wine? Nice job!
- Please pull yourself together!

304
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:53,260
Sergeant Saotome!

305
00:16:53,260 --> 00:16:55,040
He's fine!

306
00:16:59,880 --> 00:17:02,160
What's wrong?

307
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:05,130
Why are you getting transferred?

308
00:17:05,130 --> 00:17:07,010
It's not fair!

309
00:17:07,010 --> 00:17:08,800
There is nothing we can do.

310
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:11,780
We are the company's employees, after all.

311
00:17:13,780 --> 00:17:16,250
Cheer up!

312
00:17:16,250 --> 00:17:19,520
Why am I cheering you up?

313
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:27,860
I'm glad you have Koichi.

314
00:17:28,750 --> 00:17:31,240
When you go home and talk to him,

315
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:35,330
I'm sure you'll feel better.

316
00:17:35,330 --> 00:17:37,960
Maybe.

317
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:42,280
Well, we're heading home.

318
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:44,020
Thank you for everything!

319
00:17:44,020 --> 00:17:47,140
You won't be getting any sleep tonight, right? Good luck.

320
00:17:49,300 --> 00:17:50,790
- Have a good night!
- Have a good night!

321
00:17:50,790 --> 00:17:53,050
Have a good night!

322
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:57,140
Thanks, guys.

323
00:17:57,140 --> 00:17:59,120
We'll figure out the rest.

324
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:00,950
You go home, Master Sergeant Obara.

325
00:18:00,950 --> 00:18:03,250
Sorry.

326
00:18:03,250 --> 00:18:06,360
<i>Your wife will pick you up.</i>

327
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:10,490
<i>- It's not free.
- Wait a minute.</i>

328
00:18:10,490 --> 00:18:12,540
<i>What time will you be home?</i>

329
00:18:12,540 --> 00:18:16,010
Don't sleep in the store.

330
00:18:16,010 --> 00:18:17,870
Grand Sergeant Obara!

331
00:18:20,550 --> 00:18:23,560
Can I talk to you?

332
00:18:24,850 --> 00:18:26,130
About what?

333
00:18:26,130 --> 00:18:28,850
I'd like some advice about something!

334
00:18:33,980 --> 00:18:36,620
I'm sorry, I have to go home.

335
00:18:36,620 --> 00:18:38,830
Ask me another time.

336
00:18:41,070 --> 00:18:42,780
- Okay.
- Excuse me.

337
00:18:45,570 --> 00:18:47,580
What? It won't stop.

338
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:14,280
Are you okay?

339
00:19:15,710 --> 00:19:17,160
What's that?

340
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:20,720
My subordinate put it on me at the drinking party.

341
00:19:21,750 --> 00:19:23,260
A drinking party, right?

342
00:19:23,260 --> 00:19:24,310
I get it.

343
00:19:24,310 --> 00:19:27,690
I get it, I went easy on how much I drank.

344
00:19:27,690 --> 00:19:29,680
You don't get it at all!

345
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:31,410
We're going on a trip tomorrow.

346
00:19:31,410 --> 00:19:34,210
Who do you think we're going for?

347
00:19:36,780 --> 00:19:38,600
Are you listening to me?

348
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:40,090
I'm listening.

349
00:19:40,090 --> 00:19:43,600
- You're asleep.
- I'm awake!

350
00:19:52,150 --> 00:19:55,310
Come on, wake up.

351
00:19:55,310 --> 00:19:56,950
You can't sleep here!

352
00:19:56,950 --> 00:19:59,270
I am awake.

353
00:20:01,770 --> 00:20:04,860
We really aren't compatible, are we?

354
00:20:04,860 --> 00:20:07,430
To that...

355
00:20:07,430 --> 00:20:09,400
I would agree.

356
00:20:10,850 --> 00:20:14,420
You never did tell me why you married me.

357
00:20:14,420 --> 00:20:19,050
Koichi, you totally just married me on a whim, didn't you?

358
00:20:22,690 --> 00:20:25,110
We have to get your mom back quickly.

359
00:20:25,110 --> 00:20:27,840
We can't get a divorce in this mess.

360
00:20:53,010 --> 00:20:54,700
Luggage loading, complete.

361
00:20:54,700 --> 00:20:58,470
The side mirror, angled properly. We'll go at it piecemeal.

362
00:20:58,470 --> 00:21:00,840
- Piecemeal?
- Drink purchase, complete.

363
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:03,050
It's currently...

364
00:21:03,050 --> 00:21:04,580
the perfect temperature!

365
00:21:10,760 --> 00:21:13,730
Good weather, clear visibility, wind speed at eight knots.

366
00:21:13,730 --> 00:21:15,970
Thirty-one miles to our destination, Hakone.

367
00:21:15,970 --> 00:21:17,500
Estimated time of arrival, 1030 hours.

368
00:21:17,500 --> 00:21:19,980
Visiting local tourist spots is possible upon request.

369
00:21:19,980 --> 00:21:21,900
Hakone Shrine. Ashinoko Lake.

370
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:25,510
The Little Prince Museum. What do you think?

371
00:21:27,180 --> 00:21:28,910
Are you listening to me?

372
00:21:30,280 --> 00:21:31,620
<i>[Sis]</i>

373
00:21:32,890 --> 00:21:34,320
Hello?

374
00:21:34,320 --> 00:21:37,380
<i>Hey, you guys have a coffee maker at home, right?</i>

375
00:21:37,380 --> 00:21:39,710
- What?
- <i>Where are your coffee beans?</i>

376
00:21:39,710 --> 00:21:41,400
On the shelf next to the fridge.

377
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:42,910
<i>The shelf next to the fridge.</i>

378
00:21:42,910 --> 00:21:45,180
Why are you asking about our coffee beans?

379
00:21:45,180 --> 00:21:46,380
<i>Found it!</i>

380
00:21:46,380 --> 00:21:48,740
- It's this, right?
- Yes. Thank you.

381
00:21:48,740 --> 00:21:52,600
- Mom invited me over, so I came with Azusa.
- What?

382
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:55,300
I found Pierre Ledent chocolates!

383
00:21:55,300 --> 00:21:57,010
Really?

384
00:21:57,010 --> 00:21:59,730
They've got champagne too, you know.

385
00:21:59,730 --> 00:22:02,250
Hey! You can't just rummage through someone else's house!

386
00:22:02,250 --> 00:22:05,310
Listen, Azusa and I will be staying here for a little while.

387
00:22:05,310 --> 00:22:06,850
What? Why?

388
00:22:06,850 --> 00:22:09,380
What? I'm worried about Mom!

389
00:22:09,380 --> 00:22:12,240
Sorry, but we'll be here for a bit.

390
00:22:12,240 --> 00:22:13,900
Bye!

391
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:16,060
Hold on a second, Kaede-

392
00:22:18,530 --> 00:22:20,910
Your sister...

393
00:22:20,910 --> 00:22:22,550
is at our house too?

394
00:22:22,550 --> 00:22:25,570
Your family launches an attack with terrifying speed!

395
00:22:25,570 --> 00:22:27,780
As fast as an F-15!

396
00:22:29,150 --> 00:22:31,040
<i>[Jinya]</i>

397
00:22:31,040 --> 00:22:33,010
It's Jinya.

398
00:22:34,250 --> 00:22:35,910
Jinya.

399
00:22:44,420 --> 00:22:45,510
Wait!

400
00:22:45,510 --> 00:22:47,210
I'm not mentally prepared.

401
00:22:47,210 --> 00:22:51,170
You're saying this now? Why do you think we came here?

402
00:22:51,170 --> 00:22:52,340
Stop!

403
00:22:52,340 --> 00:22:56,240
Mr. and Mrs. Obara! Welcome.

404
00:22:57,410 --> 00:23:01,020
Thank you for choosing our inn for your trip.

405
00:23:01,020 --> 00:23:03,130
- We're excited to be here.
- We're excited to be here.

406
00:23:03,130 --> 00:23:05,400
Your room is this way.

407
00:23:06,060 --> 00:23:09,420
Mr. Shigemori comes here often.

408
00:23:09,420 --> 00:23:13,500
He said, "It's their honeymoon, so give them my regards!"

409
00:23:13,500 --> 00:23:15,500
Officer Shigemori?

410
00:23:20,650 --> 00:23:22,020
<i>[Congratulations on your honeymoon!]</i>

411
00:23:22,020 --> 00:23:24,880
It's a present from Mr. Shigemori!

412
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:27,320
Here's the bedroom!

413
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:29,210
What a lovely room!

414
00:23:29,210 --> 00:23:31,900
It looks like we'll have good memories from this honeymoon!

415
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:35,130
Also... the open-air bath!

416
00:23:35,130 --> 00:23:37,790
It's set to a good temperature.

417
00:23:37,790 --> 00:23:39,290
This way, please.

418
00:23:39,290 --> 00:23:42,240
Husband, you're looking stiff! Here I go!

419
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:43,660
Okay!

420
00:23:43,660 --> 00:23:46,810
- What are we doing?
- Tell me about it.

421
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:52,560
It's koi.

422
00:23:53,540 --> 00:23:56,390
Hey, isn't that your mom?

423
00:24:00,230 --> 00:24:01,410
Wonderful!

424
00:24:01,410 --> 00:24:03,400
Thank you.

425
00:24:04,090 --> 00:24:09,330
This is... a...

426
00:24:10,390 --> 00:24:15,110
I-It's a very famous Japanese novel

427
00:24:15,110 --> 00:24:20,230
written by Murasaki Shikibu a thousand years ago!

428
00:24:20,230 --> 00:24:24,020
That's so cool! Isn't it?

429
00:24:24,020 --> 00:24:25,720
Your mom...

430
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:28,900
looks so energetic.

431
00:24:31,480 --> 00:24:33,490
It's so beautiful.

432
00:24:48,350 --> 00:24:49,680
It's salty!

433
00:24:49,680 --> 00:24:51,410
It's wrong!

434
00:25:00,810 --> 00:25:04,140
Hello, I'm Mizuguchi.

435
00:25:04,140 --> 00:25:06,650
We last met at the wedding reception, right?

436
00:25:06,650 --> 00:25:09,400
Thank you for taking care of Saki.

437
00:25:10,410 --> 00:25:12,860
Pardon me!

438
00:25:12,860 --> 00:25:14,990
What should I do with this?

439
00:25:14,990 --> 00:25:16,680
Come in!

440
00:25:19,940 --> 00:25:22,510
Oh my, my, my...

441
00:25:26,620 --> 00:25:27,780
Are you getting a divorce?

442
00:25:27,780 --> 00:25:29,910
- No I'm not!
- But...

443
00:25:29,910 --> 00:25:32,480
My wife just put that there on her own.

444
00:25:33,590 --> 00:25:35,270
- Don't touch it!
- Oh my god!

445
00:25:35,270 --> 00:25:37,010
Please.

446
00:25:38,020 --> 00:25:41,290
If you touch it, I feel like it will become reality.

447
00:25:42,100 --> 00:25:45,780
Actually, my wife left too.

448
00:25:45,780 --> 00:25:47,820
Want a drink?

449
00:25:47,820 --> 00:25:50,660
I got my hands on some good mullet roe.

450
00:25:50,660 --> 00:25:52,790
Let's drink, let's drink!

451
00:25:52,790 --> 00:25:55,280
What the hell are they thinking?

452
00:25:55,280 --> 00:25:57,510
<i>Our wives, that is.</i>

453
00:25:59,110 --> 00:26:00,460
<i>I feel exactly the same!</i>

454
00:26:00,460 --> 00:26:02,320
I retired,

455
00:26:02,320 --> 00:26:07,280
and I finally thought I could be with my wife, and she leaves!

456
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:08,770
It's ridiculous!

457
00:26:08,770 --> 00:26:12,010
And hasn't she been living on your salary until you retired?

458
00:26:12,010 --> 00:26:13,100
Yeah, exactly.

459
00:26:13,100 --> 00:26:16,290
But the second you retired, she tossed you to the side.

460
00:26:16,290 --> 00:26:18,420
You're in the same situation as me, right?

461
00:26:18,420 --> 00:26:20,370
My wife?

462
00:26:20,370 --> 00:26:22,350
She was free as a bird from the start.

463
00:26:22,350 --> 00:26:26,550
Beause a worthy man will let his wife be free.

464
00:26:26,550 --> 00:26:30,530
Are you saying I was too controlling with my wife?

465
00:26:30,530 --> 00:26:34,010
Now, now...

466
00:26:34,010 --> 00:26:35,820
Listen to this!

467
00:26:35,820 --> 00:26:37,470
I...

468
00:26:38,090 --> 00:26:39,270
bought this.

469
00:26:39,270 --> 00:26:41,260
"Divorce Prep Tips."

470
00:26:41,260 --> 00:26:43,150
Did he write anything useful?

471
00:26:43,150 --> 00:26:47,170
Why are you acting so eager?

472
00:26:47,170 --> 00:26:48,280
It's for you.

473
00:26:48,280 --> 00:26:49,670
Really?

474
00:26:49,670 --> 00:26:52,000
Well...

475
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:54,350
<i>"Don't suddenly leave your home."</i>

476
00:26:54,350 --> 00:26:58,510
No way! You already left!

477
00:26:58,510 --> 00:27:00,790
What should I do?

478
00:27:00,790 --> 00:27:04,630
"First, lay the necessary groundwork behind the scenes."

479
00:27:04,630 --> 00:27:06,620
"Gather evidence of infidelity,

480
00:27:06,620 --> 00:27:09,850
get everything in order, and then leave your home."

481
00:27:09,850 --> 00:27:13,850
"This is the right way to get a divorce."

482
00:27:13,850 --> 00:27:16,850
All of a sudden, we're on the wrong foot.

483
00:27:16,850 --> 00:27:20,780
Say, maybe you should go talk to a lawyer?

484
00:27:20,780 --> 00:27:25,040
I don't know any lawyers!

485
00:27:30,780 --> 00:27:32,540
<i>Are you okay?</i>

486
00:27:33,150 --> 00:27:34,950
Yeah.

487
00:27:34,950 --> 00:27:39,110
<i>Excuse me, I've brought your dinner.</i>

488
00:27:44,830 --> 00:27:46,750
Your mom.

489
00:27:50,730 --> 00:27:53,290
Here's a spring-themed, multi-course appetizer.

490
00:27:53,290 --> 00:27:55,420
Inside these ducks is mugwort leaf tofu.

491
00:27:55,420 --> 00:27:58,010
- Mom!
- The gardens here...

492
00:27:58,530 --> 00:28:00,910
Please come back home.

493
00:28:03,950 --> 00:28:06,460
Dad is waiting for you!

494
00:28:06,460 --> 00:28:08,300
And this is a sakura shrimp omelet...

495
00:28:08,300 --> 00:28:10,210
Mom!

496
00:28:16,260 --> 00:28:18,250
Excuse me!

497
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:25,020
Did something happen?

498
00:28:25,020 --> 00:28:27,230
No, it was nothing.

499
00:28:27,780 --> 00:28:30,360
I brought beer.

500
00:28:36,320 --> 00:28:38,450
Please enjoy.

501
00:28:38,450 --> 00:28:40,550
Excuse me.

502
00:29:11,620 --> 00:29:14,350
I just took a bath.

503
00:29:14,940 --> 00:29:16,720
Okay.

504
00:29:16,720 --> 00:29:18,980
Why don't you go in too?

505
00:29:23,700 --> 00:29:26,550
Don't feel like it, right?

506
00:29:29,420 --> 00:29:31,870
Now I'm confused.

507
00:29:31,870 --> 00:29:33,030
What is it?

508
00:29:33,030 --> 00:29:37,320
Who was the mother I knew my whole life?

509
00:29:39,050 --> 00:29:41,120
Maybe...

510
00:29:42,060 --> 00:29:45,760
she really was unhappy the whole time.

511
00:29:46,710 --> 00:29:49,340
Was she always putting up with it?

512
00:29:49,340 --> 00:29:51,480
Because of me?

513
00:29:58,600 --> 00:30:00,220
Rain.

514
00:30:10,020 --> 00:30:14,660
When you were a kid, and it rained,

515
00:30:14,660 --> 00:30:17,720
would your mom come pick you up with an umbrella?

516
00:30:17,720 --> 00:30:19,820
Yeah.

517
00:30:19,820 --> 00:30:21,710
I thought so.

518
00:30:21,710 --> 00:30:23,810
It was fine when I was in elementary school,

519
00:30:23,810 --> 00:30:27,930
but she even came to get me in Junior High. It was embarrassing.

520
00:30:28,520 --> 00:30:31,200
She's a good cook too.

521
00:30:31,200 --> 00:30:35,210
The omelet I had when we went to your parents' house before,

522
00:30:35,210 --> 00:30:37,520
it was beautifully round,

523
00:30:37,520 --> 00:30:39,260
and the sweetness was delicious.

524
00:30:39,260 --> 00:30:41,130
It's my dad's favorite.

525
00:30:41,130 --> 00:30:44,750
I had it so many times, but I'll never get tired of it.

526
00:30:44,750 --> 00:30:46,320
But...

527
00:30:47,080 --> 00:30:49,560
really, my mom

528
00:30:50,100 --> 00:30:53,500
doesn't like sweet omelets.

529
00:30:54,640 --> 00:30:58,190
She always put up with it for the family's sake.

530
00:30:59,300 --> 00:31:01,410
She's kind.

531
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:03,690
Yeah.

532
00:31:03,690 --> 00:31:07,740
But she was really strict about manners.

533
00:31:07,740 --> 00:31:10,350
"Don't cause anyone any trouble."

534
00:31:10,350 --> 00:31:14,850
"If someone's in trouble, help them!"

535
00:31:14,850 --> 00:31:17,200
She's a good mom.

536
00:31:21,060 --> 00:31:24,120
But she wants to reset everything,

537
